          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Filtered neutron beams at the piercing channel of",
                "the Dalat reactor were used. Its parameters:",
                "Thermal neutrons with 98cmSi+10cmTi+ 35g/cm2S filter",
                "combination and 1.8 x 10**7 n/cm2/s neutron flux",
                "144 keV neutrons with 98cmSi+10cmTi+ 0.2g/cm2B10 filter",
                "combination and 1.2 x 10**7 n/cm2/s neutron flux",
                "55 keV neutrons with 98cmSi+35g/cm2S+0.2g/cm2B10 filter",
                "combination and 4.0 x 10**6 n/cm2/s neutron flux"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural uramium sample. Experiments are performed",
                "with 197Au foils as a standard that is irradiated",
                "simultaneously with 238U foils. The thickness of",
                "238U foils is approximately 0.276 g/cm2 and",
                "0.087g/cm2 for 197Au-foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
